narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: How to work in a group class setting.
This class really helped me grow as a writer in a more journalistic style. I was able to branch out from academic writing.
I learned how to write a variety of different styles and how to change my voice as an author for my purpose.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: In this class you grow as a reader, and get positive critical criticism .
Theres a lot of room to explore topics youre interested, and there is a lot of really helpful feedback.
I think being more clear about which of the readings we are going to be working with would be good so I could focus on just those readings.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! A really great chance to use a course to really explore whatever topics you want and build your writing skills.
I would recommend this course to another student because you really get to develop relationships with your professors and classmates.
Definitely, great units taught by a great professor

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
How will you use the knowledge and skills you learned in this course in your future endeavors?
comments: I will better respond in group class settings.
I learned how to be confident in myself as a writer.
